HEADWORD: Myxoedema
<hw>Myx`oe*de"ma</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. fr. Gr.
<?/ mucus + <ets>oedema</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A disease
producing a peculiar cretinoid appearance of the face, slow speech, and
dullness of intellect, and due to failure of the functions of the
thyroid gland.</def> <altsp>[Also spelled
<asp>myxedema</asp>.]</altsp>-- <wordforms><wf>Myx`oe*dem"a*tous</wf>
<pr>(#)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>, <wf>Myx`oe*dem"ic</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Myxoma</ent>⟦br⟧
